

        String name = "  chuck norris ";

        name = name.toUpperCase().trim();
        name = name.charAt(0) + "." + name.charAt(name.indexOf(" ") + 1) + ".";
        System.out.println(name);






By using string literal ---> String str = "Hello Yalcin";
By using new keyword ---> String str1 = new String ("Hello Yalcin");




What happens if you don't initialize an array?

The array elements will be initialized to their default values.
For primitive data types:
byte, short, int, long, float, double, char =  0
boolean = false
For non-primitive :
object references = null